'''布朗主义'''（'''Brownism'''）是一个[[英国|英国]]政治术语，它最早由[[BBC|BBC]]记者{{le|马克·伊斯顿|Mark Easton}}提出，用来描述[[戈登·布朗|戈登·布朗]]的[[政治意识形态|政治意识形态]].<ref name="intro-cam">{{cite news|last=Easton|first=Mark|title=卡梅伦主义正在形成|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-14115047|accessdate=11 July 2011|newspaper=BBC News UK|date=11 July 2011|authorlink=Mark Easton|quote=[[Majorism|Majorism]] and Brownism are unconvincing stubs. History appears to have decided they may have re-upholstered the settee and scattered a few cushions but they didn't alter the [[feng_shui|feng shui]] of the room.|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308012017/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-14115047|dead-url=no}}</ref>

支持布朗主义相关的人被称为“布朗主义者”，这个词被用来描述意识形态上接近布朗的人。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_uAXAQAAIAAJ&hl=en&dq=brownite&ei=dupITOHjHqWX4gbF3NiZDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=4&ved=0CDUQ6AEwAzgU |title=The New Statesman, Volume 21, Issues 1036–1049, p 11 |access-date=2016-12-27 |archive-date=2016-05-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160502200800/https://books.google.com/books?id=_uAXAQAAIAAJ&hl=en&dq=brownite&ei=dupITOHjHqWX4gbF3NiZDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=4&ved=0CDUQ6AEwAzgU |dead-url=no }}</ref>一般情况下，经常被用作布莱尔主义—形容[[托尼·布莱尔|托尼·布莱尔]]政治意识形态的词汇—的反义词。<br />
在一篇公开发表的文章中，社会学家[[安东尼·吉登斯|安东尼·吉登斯]]认为，与[[布莱尔主义|布莱尔主义]]不同，布朗主义者对市场驱动的改革，如学费改革和建立市场化的基金会医院，往往不那么热心，而更热衷于国家的作用，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.newstatesman.com/uk-politics/2010/05/labour-policy-policies-blair |title=新工党的兴衰 |publisher=New Statesman |date=17 May 2010 |accessdate=23 July 2010 |archive-date=2015-07-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150721071041/http://www.newstatesman.com/uk-politics/2010/05/labour-policy-policies-blair |dead-url=no }}</ref>不太关心工党与工会的联系<ref name="autogenerated1">{{cite news |last=Jones |first=Nicholas |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk_politics/5323960.stm |title=UK | UK Politics | 布朗主义大战布莱尔主义 – the full story |publisher=BBC News |date=7 September 2006 |accessdate=23 July 2010 |archive-date=2007-08-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070827154932/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk_politics/5323960.stm |dead-url=no }}</ref>并批评媒体管理技术，如使用[[政治化妆师|政治化妆师]]。<ref name="autogenerated1"/>{{le|Will Hutton}}认为：“像托尼·布莱尔一样，戈登·布朗是一个多元化和公平的社会以及[[社会流动性|社会流动]]的信徒，并将经济效率与社会正义结合起来。”<ref name="guardian2006">{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2006/jun/21/post164 |title=如何击败布莱尔:成为布莱尔主义者 | Comment is free | guardian.co.uk |publisher=Guardian |date=21 June 2006 |accessdate=23 July 2010 |location=London |first=Will |last=Hutton |archive-date=2021-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308134211/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2006/jun/21/post164 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

